  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">No Azure Functions — use `BackgroundService` (`Microsoft.Extensions.Hosting`) for the scheduled + signal-driven cleanup loop. Existing canonical examples: `ServiceBusJobProcessor`, `PlaybookIndexingBackgroundService`, `ScheduledRagIndexingService`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism — register the `BackgroundService` AND the signal service inside `AnalysisServicesModule.cs` via `services.AddHostedService<SessionFilesCleanupJob>()` (precedent: line 325 already registers `PlaybookSchedulerService`). ZERO new top-level `Program.cs` lines. Concrete classes by default; no new interface unless a genuine seam is required (the signal service WILL get a tiny `ISessionFilesCleanupSignal` interface to keep `ChatSessionManager` testable — that is the single allowed seam; document the rationale).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">All R5 endpoints + services in BFF only. This task adds an `IHostedService` + signal helper inside the BFF; NO endpoint, NO new service extraction.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">Per-document deletion filters MUST be `tenantId eq '...' and sessionId eq '...'` — both predicates required. The job MUST NOT delete cross-tenant by `sessionId` alone. Tenant isolation contract is binding.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-018">R5 introduces NO new feature flags. The cleanup job runs unconditionally inside the `if (analysisEnabled && documentIntelligenceEnabled)` compound gate (precedent: `PlaybookSchedulerService`). Kill-switch coverage inherits from the existing compound gate via the parent module.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">BFF publish hygiene — verify publish-size delta per task. Run `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`; report absolute size + delta vs prior baseline in task notes. Expected ≤ +0.1 MB.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 (Reuse Mandate)">MUST follow the existing `BackgroundService` + `PeriodicTimer` pattern in `ScheduledRagIndexingService` AND the `Channel`-based queue pattern in `PlaybookIndexingService`/`PlaybookIndexingBackgroundService`. MUST NOT introduce a parallel job-scheduling framework, Hangfire, Quartz, or any external scheduler dependency.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.2">NO new feature flags. Schedule cadence + on/off behavior controlled by `SessionFilesCleanupOptions` (binding config section); no `SessionFilesCleanup:Enabled` flag — the service registration itself is the kill-switch, gated by the existing compound AI gate.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.3">Hosted service + signal helper registered inside `AnalysisServicesModule.cs`. ZERO new top-level `Program.cs` lines. The compound gate `if (analysisEnabled && documentIntelligenceEnabled)` already covers the registration; insert below the existing `Console.WriteLine("✓ Analysis services enabled")` line.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.6">Per-task BFF publish-size verification mandatory. Report absolute + delta in task notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.7">Tests in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/SessionFilesCleanupJobTests.cs` MUST be added. Existing `ChatSessionManagerTests.cs` MUST be updated for the new fire-and-forget `SignalSessionEnded` call (verify the new signal injection is null-tolerant — the manager MUST NOT fail if the cleanup signal is absent in tests).</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-02">Aggressive cleanup on session-end (no scheduled-sweep delay) — the on-session-end signal path MUST issue the delete WITHIN seconds of `DeleteSessionAsync` returning. Idempotent: re-running the delete on an already-evicted session is a no-op + emits a zero-count metric.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-03">Multi-tenancy — per-tenant scans + per-tenant delete filters. Cross-tenant cleanup is a defect.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project (idempotency)">Idempotent re-runs MUST succeed without throwing. A second invocation against an already-evicted `(tenantId, sessionId)` MUST: (a) issue the filtered query, (b) find 0 matching documents, (c) skip the delete batch, (d) emit `documents_deleted: 0` telemetry, (e) return success.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project (back-compat)">`ChatSessionManager.DeleteSessionAsync` signature MUST remain byte-for-byte unchanged. The new `SignalSessionEnded` call is fire-and-forget at the end of `DeleteSessionAsync` (after Redis remove + Dataverse archive + Cosmos delete); a thrown signal-service exception MUST NOT propagate (log-and-swallow per fire-and-forget convention already used for Cosmos persist in the same method).</constraint>
    <constraint source=".claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md">Per BFF additions governance — this task adds a new `IHostedService` + helper inside BFF. Placement justification: cleanup is tightly coupled to BFF-owned session + index plumbing; extraction would require crossing the chat-session manager / AI-search infrastructure boundary — not justified. Cite this in PR description per §10 binding workflow rule.</constraint>
  </constraints>

