      property has landed). Read `current-task.md` to verify no conflicting R5
      task is in flight. Read project README for project status.
    </step>

    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read every file listed in &lt;inputs&gt; and &lt;knowledge&gt;. Specifically:
      - Read `ServiceBusJobProcessor.cs`, `PlaybookIndexingBackgroundService.cs`,
        and `ScheduledRagIndexingService.cs` end-to-end to internalize the three
        canonical patterns (Service Bus shape, channel-signal shape, periodic-timer
        shape).
      - Read `AnalysisServicesModule.cs` lines around the existing
        `AddHostedService&lt;PlaybookSchedulerService&gt;` call (line 325) — this
        is the registration site.
      - Read `ChatSessionManager.DeleteSessionAsync` (lines 198–232) to confirm
        the fire-and-forget Cosmos-persist convention to mirror for the new
        `SignalSessionEnded` call.
      - Read `AiSearchOptions.cs` to confirm `SessionFilesIndexName` exists
        (added by task 003) and its default value.
      - Read `AiTelemetry.cs` to identify the existing event-emission API
        (likely an `EmitEvent` or `RecordEvent` method).
      - Read ADR-014, ADR-018, ADR-010 in full.
      - Read R5 CLAUDE.md §§3.1, 3.2, 3.3, 3.6, 3.7 and spec NFR-02.
    </step>

    <step order="3" name="Locate Active-Session Source of Truth">
      Determine HOW the scheduled pass discovers active sessions. Options:
      (a) `IConnectionMultiplexer.GetServer().Keys(pattern: "chat:session:*")` —
      Redis-direct key enumeration; works but pricey on large key sets and
      requires `IConnectionMultiplexer` injection (verify it's already
      registered unconditionally). (b) A tenant-scoped session-key registry
      Sorted Set if one exists (search for `chat:session-registry` or similar).
      (c) Dataverse `sprk_aichatsummary` table query for non-archived sessions.

      RECOMMENDED: (a) Redis key scan with the `chat:session:` pattern, gated
      on the same `IDistributedCache` Redis backend the manager uses. Performance
      acceptable at session counts &lt; 100k per tenant; if scaling becomes a
      concern, a future task can add a registry Sorted Set.

      Record the decision + rationale in task notes. If `IConnectionMultiplexer`
      is conditionally registered, fall back to option (c) Dataverse query.
    </step>

    <step order="4" name="Plan Implementation">
      Decompose into 6 subtasks:
      1. Add `SessionFilesCleanupOptions` (binding config) + `ISessionFilesCleanupSignal` + `SessionFilesCleanupSignal` (concrete; channel-owning singleton).
      2. Add `SessionFilesCleanupJob : BackgroundService` with scheduled + signal-driven loops + shared `EvictSessionAsync` helper.
      3. Register the trio inside `AnalysisServicesModule.cs` under the existing compound gate (immediately below the `PlaybookSchedulerService` registration).
      4. Wire `ChatSessionManager.DeleteSessionAsync` fire-and-forget signal call (null-tolerant injection).
      5. Add unit tests for idempotency, on-session-end signal, scheduled scan orphan detection, per-tenant isolation, zero-results no-op, ChatSessionManager null-tolerance.
      6. Run build + publish-size + CVE + quality gates.

      Acknowledge `SessionFilesCleanupJob.cs` will live at
      `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SessionFilesCleanupJob.cs`
      per R5 CLAUDE.md §8 path table (chat-session lifecycle ownership). Co-locate
      `SessionFilesCleanupSignal.cs` + `ISessionFilesCleanupSignal.cs` +
      `SessionFilesCleanupOptions.cs` in the same folder for cohesion.
    </step>

    <step order="5" name="Implement — Options + Signal Helper">
      Create `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SessionFilesCleanupOptions.cs`:

      ```csharp
      public class SessionFilesCleanupOptions
      {
          public const string SectionName = "SessionFilesCleanup";

          /// &lt;summary&gt;Hours between scheduled cleanup runs. Default 6.&lt;/summary&gt;
          public int IntervalHours { get; set; } = 6;

          /// &lt;summary&gt;Max documents deleted per batch call. Default 1000 (AI Search SDK limit).&lt;/summary&gt;
          public int DeleteBatchSize { get; set; } = 1000;

          /// &lt;summary&gt;Max session keys scanned per tenant per scheduled run. Default 10000.&lt;/summary&gt;
          public int MaxKeysPerScan { get; set; } = 10_000;
      }
      ```

      Create `ISessionFilesCleanupSignal.cs` + `SessionFilesCleanupSignal.cs`:

      ```csharp
      public interface ISessionFilesCleanupSignal
      {
          void SignalSessionEnded(string tenantId, string sessionId);
      }

      // Concrete: owns Channel&lt;SessionEndSignal&gt; (unbounded, single-reader).
      // Writer-side: TryWrite from producers (ChatSessionManager).
      // Reader-side: ChannelReader exposed via internal property for the
      // BackgroundService (same package; InternalsVisibleTo on test assembly).
      public sealed class SessionFilesCleanupSignal : ISessionFilesCleanupSignal
      {
          private readonly Channel&lt;SessionEndSignal&gt; _channel =
              Channel.CreateUnbounded&lt;SessionEndSignal&gt;(new UnboundedChannelOptions
              {
                  SingleReader = true,
                  SingleWriter = false,
              });

          internal ChannelReader&lt;SessionEndSignal&gt; Reader =&gt; _channel.Reader;

          public void SignalSessionEnded(string tenantId, string sessionId)
          {
              if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(tenantId) || string.IsNullOrEmpty(sessionId)) return;
              _channel.Writer.TryWrite(new SessionEndSignal(tenantId, sessionId));
          }
      }

      internal readonly record struct SessionEndSignal(string TenantId, string SessionId);
      ```
    </step>

    <step order="6" name="Implement — SessionFilesCleanupJob BackgroundService">
      Create `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SessionFilesCleanupJob.cs`
      following the `ScheduledRagIndexingService` shape, modified to drain the
      signal channel alongside the periodic timer. Constructor injects:
      `IServiceProvider serviceProvider, IOptions&lt;SessionFilesCleanupOptions&gt; options,
      SessionFilesCleanupSignal signal, ILogger&lt;SessionFilesCleanupJob&gt; logger`.

      `ExecuteAsync` shape:
      1. Read `_options.IntervalHours`; create `PeriodicTimer(TimeSpan.FromHours(_options.IntervalHours))`.
      2. Log startup line.
      3. Loop until cancellation:
         a. Build a `Task` racing `timer.WaitForNextTickAsync(stoppingToken)` against
            `_signal.Reader.WaitToReadAsync(stoppingToken).AsTask()`.
         b. `await Task.WhenAny(timerTask, signalTask)`.
         c. If signal won: drain all pending signals via
            `while (_signal.Reader.TryRead(out var sig))` and call
            `EvictSessionAsync(sig.TenantId, sig.SessionId, scope, "on_session_end", stoppingToken)`
            for each.
         d. If timer won: call `RunScheduledScanAsync(scope, stoppingToken)`.
      4. Catch `OperationCanceledException` on shutdown; log "Stopped".

      Per-run scope: `using var scope = _serviceProvider.CreateScope();` resolve
      `SearchIndexClient`, `IOptions&lt;AiSearchOptions&gt;`, `AiTelemetry`, optionally
      `IConnectionMultiplexer` (or `IDistributedCache` + Redis-direct API).

      `RunScheduledScanAsync`:
      1. Enumerate tenants via the configured session-key registry pattern
         (Step 3 decision). For each tenant:
         a. List distinct `sessionId` facet values from the
            `spaarke-session-files` index filtered by `tenantId eq '{tenant}'`
            (Azure Search `facets: ["sessionId,count:0"]` to get all distinct values).
         b. List active Redis keys matching `chat:session:{tenantId}:*`; extract
            sessionIds.
         c. Compute `orphans = indexedSessionIds.Except(activeSessionIds)`.
         d. For each orphan call `EvictSessionAsync(tenantId, orphanSessionId,
            scope, "scheduled", stoppingToken)`.
      2. Emit a single `r5.session_files_cleanup.run` event with
         `trigger="scheduled"`, `sessions_evicted=orphans.Count`,
         `documents_deleted=totalDeleted`, `per_tenant_breakdown=[...]`,
         `duration_ms=stopwatch`.

      `EvictSessionAsync(tenantId, sessionId, scope, trigger, ct)`:
      1. Get `SearchClient` via
         `scope.ServiceProvider.GetRequiredService&lt;SearchIndexClient&gt;()
         .GetSearchClient(aiSearchOptions.SessionFilesIndexName)`.
      2. Build filter `tenantId eq '{escaped}' and sessionId eq '{escaped}'`.
      3. Page through matching document keys via
         `SearchAsync&lt;Dictionary&lt;string, object&gt;&gt;("*", new SearchOptions { Filter=..., Select={ "id" }, Size=1000 })`
         and collect doc keys.
      4. If `keys.Count == 0`: emit telemetry `documents_deleted: 0`; return.
      5. Batch keys into chunks of `_options.DeleteBatchSize` and call
         `client.DeleteDocumentsAsync(keyField: "id", keys: batch, ct)`.
      6. Emit `r5.session_files_cleanup.run` event with
         `trigger=trigger`, `sessions_evicted=1`, `documents_deleted=keys.Count`,
         `tenant_id=tenantId`, `session_id=sessionId`, `duration_ms=stopwatch`.

      Add `[assembly: InternalsVisibleTo("Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests")]` if not already
      present (likely is) so tests can poke at internal types/methods.
    </step>

    <step order="7" name="Implement — DI Registration in AnalysisServicesModule">
      Open `AnalysisServicesModule.cs`. Locate the existing line:
      ```csharp
      services.AddHostedService&lt;Sprk.Bff.Api.Services.PlaybookSchedulerService&gt;();
      ```
      Immediately below, inside the same `if (analysisEnabled &amp;&amp; documentIntelligenceEnabled)`
      compound gate, insert:

      ```csharp
      // R5 task 007 (D1-07) — Session-files cleanup hosted service per spec NFR-02.
      // Scheduled sweep + on-session-end immediate trigger; idempotent. Inherits
      // kill-switch from this compound gate per R5 CLAUDE.md §3.2 (no new flag).
      services.AddSingleton&lt;Sprk.Bff.Api.Services.Ai.Chat.SessionFilesCleanupSignal&gt;();
      services.AddSingleton&lt;Sprk.Bff.Api.Services.Ai.Chat.ISessionFilesCleanupSignal&gt;(
          sp =&gt; sp.GetRequiredService&lt;Sprk.Bff.Api.Services.Ai.Chat.SessionFilesCleanupSignal&gt;());
      services.Configure&lt;Sprk.Bff.Api.Services.Ai.Chat.SessionFilesCleanupOptions&gt;(
          configuration.GetSection(Sprk.Bff.Api.Services.Ai.Chat.SessionFilesCleanupOptions.SectionName));
      services.AddHostedService&lt;Sprk.Bff.Api.Services.Ai.Chat.SessionFilesCleanupJob&gt;();
      Console.WriteLine("✓ Session-files cleanup hosted service enabled (R5 task 007, NFR-02)");
      ```

      Verify ZERO new top-level `Program.cs` lines. Verify no edits outside the
      compound-gated block (registration MUST inherit the existing kill-switch).
