    <criterion testable="true">NO new feature flag introduced (per R5 CLAUDE.md §3.2). The service registers unconditionally inside the existing AI compound gate; `SessionFilesCleanupOptions` controls cadence + batch sizes but has no `Enabled` property.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Scheduled trigger fires the cleanup loop every `IntervalHours` (default 6h). Verified by unit test that drives the `PeriodicTimer` tick and asserts the scheduled-scan path executes.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">On-session-end immediate trigger works: `ChatSessionManager.DeleteSessionAsync` calls `ISessionFilesCleanupSignal.SignalSessionEnded(tenantId, sessionId)` at the end of its existing logic; the signal channel receives the message; the `BackgroundService` loop drains it and invokes `EvictSessionAsync` for that session. Verified by unit test `OnSignalReceived_drains_all_pending_signals_in_single_batch`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`ChatSessionManager.DeleteSessionAsync` signature is byte-for-byte unchanged (verified by git diff); the new signal call is fire-and-forget + log-and-swallow on failure (mirrors the existing Cosmos persist pattern); the new `cleanupSignal` constructor parameter is nullable + defaulted to null (back-compat for tests + the compound-AI-OFF path).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Delete filter on every eviction is `tenantId eq '{tenantId}' and sessionId eq '{sessionId}'` — BOTH predicates always present. Verified by unit test `EvictSession_filter_includes_both_tenantId_and_sessionId` (ADR-014 compliance).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Idempotent re-runs: invoking `EvictSessionAsync` twice for the same `(tenantId, sessionId)` succeeds without error; the second invocation returns 0 hits from the search query, skips the delete batch, and emits a zero-count telemetry event. Verified by unit test `EvictSession_invoked_twice_for_same_session_is_idempotent`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Per-tenant isolation: scheduled scan + on-session-end deletes NEVER cross tenants. Verified by unit test `ScheduledScan_per_tenant_isolation_no_cross_tenant_delete` (ADR-014 + spec NFR-03).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Scheduled scan correctly identifies orphans: indexed `sessionId` values NOT present in the active Redis session set are evicted; active sessions are untouched. Verified by unit test `ScheduledScan_evicts_only_orphans_not_in_active_set`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Telemetry event `r5.session_files_cleanup.run` emitted on every run with fields: `trigger` (scheduled|on_session_end), `sessions_evicted`, `documents_deleted`, `tenant_id` (per-tenant for on-session-end; per-tenant breakdown array for scheduled), `session_id` (on-session-end only), `duration_ms`, `completion_status` (success|partial|error). Verified by unit test `EvictSession_emits_telemetry_with_trigger_and_counts`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`SessionFilesCleanupOptions` binds to config section `SessionFilesCleanup` with defaults: `IntervalHours = 6`, `DeleteBatchSize = 1000`, `MaxKeysPerScan = 10000`. Admin-overridable per environment.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`SessionFilesCleanupSignal` is a concrete singleton owning an unbounded `Channel&lt;SessionEndSignal&gt;` (single-reader, multi-writer); the `ISessionFilesCleanupSignal` interface exposes only the producer-side `SignalSessionEnded(tenantId, sessionId)` method (consumer-side reader access is internal to the assembly per `InternalsVisibleTo`).</criterion>
